&lt;h2 id=&#34;log---june-08-2023&#34;&gt;Log - June 08 2023&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I have been studying for the TOEFL for nearly a month and have realized that several areas require improvement. While I find reading relatively manageable, I encounter difficulties in the remaining three sections. Therefore, I need to dedicate more time to practicing and refining my skills in those areas. As the application season is approaching, I am feeling increasingly anxious about the status of my TOEFL preparation. Consequently, I must set specific tasks for myself to accomplish.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The speaking section of the TOEFL is particularly challenging for non-native speakers due to the lack of a language-rich environment. Thus, it is crucial to focus on practicing this section. I plan to take the TOEFL Speaking exam daily and dedicate at least one hour each day to practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In contrast, writing and listening are comparatively easier to practice. However, it is important not to confine our efforts solely to the exam itself. It is beneficial to engage in additional activities, such as watching educational videos and writing essays on various topics and tasks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;log---aug-12-2023&#34;&gt;Log - Aug 12 2023&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After taking the test on July 22nd, I registered for another test scheduled for September 9th. From the previous test results, it&amp;rsquo;s apparent that my performance in the Listening and Speaking sections could use improvement compared to the other two sections. I&amp;rsquo;ve conducted research to find strategies for enhancing these skills, and I&amp;rsquo;m hopeful that implementing these techniques will yield positive results.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://tstprep.com/articles/toefl/ten-awesome-tips-for-the-listening-section-of-the-toefl-test/&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;Listening Section&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://tstprep.com/articles/toefl/ten-awesome-tips-for-the-listening-section-of-the-toefl-test/#create-toefl-listening-study-schedule&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tip #1&lt;/strong&gt; - Create a TOEFL Listening study schedule&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://tstprep.com/articles/toefl/ten-awesome-tips-for-the-listening-section-of-the-toefl-test/#make-eyes-enemy&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tip #2&lt;/strong&gt; - Make your eyes your enemy&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://tstprep.com/articles/toefl/ten-awesome-tips-for-the-listening-section-of-the-toefl-test/#become-toefl-listening-note-taking-pro&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tip #3&lt;/strong&gt; - Become a notetaking pro&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://tstprep.com/articles/toefl/ten-awesome-tips-for-the-listening-section-of-the-toefl-test/#memorize-toefl-listening-question-types&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tip #4&lt;/strong&gt; - Memorize the question types&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://tstprep.com/articles/toefl/ten-awesome-tips-for-the-listening-section-of-the-toefl-test/#understand-toefl-listening-passage&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tip #5&lt;/strong&gt; - Understand the passage structure like a professor&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://tstprep.com/articles/toefl/ten-awesome-tips-for-the-listening-section-of-the-toefl-test/#toefl-listening-vocabulary&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tip #6&lt;/strong&gt; - Focus on vocabulary less, story more&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://tstprep.com/articles/toefl/ten-awesome-tips-for-the-listening-section-of-the-toefl-test/#toefl-listening-be-active-listener&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tip #7&lt;/strong&gt; - Be an active listener&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://tstprep.com/articles/toefl/ten-awesome-tips-for-the-listening-section-of-the-toefl-test/#toefl-listening-think-like-teacher&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tip #8&lt;/strong&gt; - Think like a North American teacher&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://tstprep.com/articles/toefl/ten-awesome-tips-for-the-listening-section-of-the-toefl-test/#toefl-listening-track-study-process&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tip #9&lt;/strong&gt; - Track your study progress&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://tstprep.com/articles/toefl/ten-awesome-tips-for-the-listening-section-of-the-toefl-test/#toefl-listening-dont-panic&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tip #10&lt;/strong&gt; - Don&amp;rsquo;t panic&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://tstprep.com/articles/toefl/ten-awesome-tips-for-the-speaking-section-of-the-toefl/&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;Speaking Section&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://tstprep.com/articles/toefl/ten-awesome-tips-for-the-speaking-section-of-the-toefl/#tip1-practice-instead-of-videos&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tip #1&lt;/strong&gt; - Practice instead of watching videos&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://tstprep.com/articles/toefl/ten-awesome-tips-for-the-speaking-section-of-the-toefl/#tip2-record-your-voice&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tip #2&lt;/strong&gt; - Record your voice&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://tstprep.com/articles/toefl/ten-awesome-tips-for-the-speaking-section-of-the-toefl/#tip3-use-grading-rubric&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tip #3&lt;/strong&gt; - Use a grading rubric to analyze your response&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://tstprep.com/articles/toefl/ten-awesome-tips-for-the-speaking-section-of-the-toefl/#tip4-find-study-buddy&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tip #4&lt;/strong&gt; - Find a study buddy&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://tstprep.com/articles/toefl/ten-awesome-tips-for-the-speaking-section-of-the-toefl/#tip5-move-your-hands&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tip #5&lt;/strong&gt; - Move your hands when you speak&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://tstprep.com/articles/toefl/ten-awesome-tips-for-the-speaking-section-of-the-toefl/#tip6-pick-right-time-and-place&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tip #6&lt;/strong&gt; - Pick the right time and place when you study&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://tstprep.com/articles/toefl/ten-awesome-tips-for-the-speaking-section-of-the-toefl/#tip7-start-the-same&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tip #7&lt;/strong&gt; - Start the same way for each question type every time&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://tstprep.com/articles/toefl/ten-awesome-tips-for-the-speaking-section-of-the-toefl/#tip8-use-timer&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tip #8&lt;/strong&gt; - Use a timer&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://tstprep.com/articles/toefl/ten-awesome-tips-for-the-speaking-section-of-the-toefl/#tip9-use-speech-to-text&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tip #9&lt;/strong&gt; - Take advantage of speech-to-text technology&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://tstprep.com/articles/toefl/ten-awesome-tips-for-the-speaking-section-of-the-toefl/#tip10-get-teacher-support&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tip #10&lt;/strong&gt; - Get professional support from an experienced teacher&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These tips are quite motivating, but their effectiveness depends on their proper implementation and execution. With ample time remaining until the next test, I am hopeful that by following these guidelines, I can achieve the target score I am aiming for.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
